[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test class rules**\n\nI’m thinking about the rule that states all top-level test classes must be public. What about package-private non-test top-level classes? It seems better to use nested private static helpers within public tests instead. Then, I’m considering a custom in-memory component: it extends DefaultComponent and holds a Map<String, Consumer> for consumers. Maybe the endpoint.createConsumer method is where these get registered? I realize createConsumer returns a Consumer, but start/stop methods are invoked by Camel.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d4f816674c440d00169fd2a4b8b2c819da8516b3079a9f8ab\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_Spd5qFcfySIksbiIRSSXbhCaxQyJI6NSg3hzOr4i31yk91l7A4MX-q6nF5LU4idmsCoizGQ8MFTfJ0MOQo2FcM5yAj1dU0Kbw-YismT9C3c2o-VfYoS5JXRa-NnbgrKAiWzGKGaM1PGTt_VBR9i-H8vNI9iMT2w-ICu7zsH07Vx51VNb6qZGe7SWHiorVW3kbej_6fksP0Mn5KshhZr6AVQ1nWKYcKHIrZavviZoHvy9exONwlmk70e8dDZgWrev2UAB_k6JsKdOUGmDX8BDWvsyg6QsdPASAaLonPbNzxb1P1Fd0osJeVRex49c1mFC9KFiMZyY14be-kr7U0IfTeQENfL3Fsc-RciLJ7-b6f2LzSiQ_gels33Eohwnzv00inyX1xbaq8fGd_DECyAtIRBdvjEin9dugXPx1y-mcEoSU16CzTdXX7NSM13jLo5jC4TLWobbj23dZQ0aCYwE8NBr5Q7H-sftgBXva6OJBRGAYbQF2DLE6OHhCflIye8GQsvNcY8LO2wshHcNmY-R5Dq9gMTknnbtstDWfkdBSETP8QmTidtyC_9LTIQcu_bWMWf2EYz9OIdSDan6adEjW6YQjyZRwPoyIcd6nduY4eDrPC-XcEdJu-6winVZcg1yp-1TZh8ij_Dn-h8jnQxScRRTsYGY7kOZo5L7vZVg1To3I9r0qAoUCXmZpirWWJcuFKPpzyrMQRc4QBNksZQtGr26baHufxW5EB6eGwuHVa5MReJs6POJ29feMlBC972YukOB-vSsFnWr92qej3tfSmGcWkIpFuK06jyD6C2nGXnvirmCh_Bp1M-WeX0WPKzXR5wwJF36GsHPvGRTgqco2eN46FO3AOwcwyVRv8A39v9EJzD5x4m4m6gHzZNKmXWstR6T0m5bh5MGKypiSBuI34-IaYCNMojiRHZgfy-mGBjHZ75PuPEI54NHIaZLdh6tt6gazCRPPU5pz50eVyckoA604oxvOPx1NTFgdT55D7q_emC4Q9YbWCjgu27EvTrb6PqUAo09oTmnIdS5OCk5AaC_zhQxWN6yf2tCLhJrT16bqRI3q8EvfgPV4mqM441jiOcMTj6TaVABza5X4UKCDTUPvOn4w-GByHAyTIvkyjCQyzp_ZSn6kxT_QVfkWrRr8K3IQLy4NnEULLhlcSle0YhJp-sCol9_FMnRxwvelXR4Oo